Vegetation Patterns - Code¶

Creating the Grid:¶

  • In the Real Space:
In [ ]:
L0=10**2 # The size of the Grid

N=400 # Number of points I'm using

dx=L0/N # Space between points - X direction
dy=L0/N # Space between points - Y direction

x = np.arange(-L0/2, L0/2, dx) # X axis
y = np.arange(-L0/2, L0/2, dy) # Y axis

X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)   # Two Grids with the values of X and Y in every point of the Grid

## Ex: if x=[0,1,2] and y=[0,1,2]
##
##    [0,1,2]    [2,2,2]
##  X=[0,1,2]  Y=[1,1,1]
##    [0,1,2]    [0,0,0]
  • In the Fourier Space
In [ ]:
# The Fourier coordinates
kx=2*np.pi*np.fft.fftfreq(N,d=dx) 
ky=2*np.pi*np.fft.fftfreq(N,d=dy)

K, L = np.meshgrid(kx, ky) # Two Grids with the values of kx and ky in every point of the Grid

Rk = np.sqrt((K)**2 +(L)**2) # The "radius" of the Fourier coordinates
# Basically:

$R_k = |\vec{k}|$

Time, Parameters and Initial Condition:¶

## Initial Condition:
rh0=(np.array([[random.rand() for i in range(N)] for j in range(N)]) -0.5)*0.1 + (beta-alpha)/(beta+alpha*delta)
  • Parameters:

$\beta_0 = 1.0\\ \alpha=0.5 \\ \delta=17 \\ R=8 \\q=1$

  • Initial condition:

$\rho_0 = Rand() + \rho^{*}$

Whereby: $\rho^{*} = \dfrac{\beta_0-\alpha}{\beta_0 + \alpha\delta},$

and:: $Rand() = $ A grid of uniformly distributed random numbers on the interval: $[-0.05,0.05]$

Functions:¶

Defining $\hat{G}(\vec{k})$:¶

$\hat{G}(\vec{k})= 2 \dfrac{J_{1}(|\vec{k}|R)}{|\vec{k}|R}$

  • Whereby $J_1(x)$ is the rst-order Bessel function.
In [175]:
def G_hat(Rk,R):
    G_hat=2*spc.j1(Rk*R)/(Rk*R) #spc.j1() is the bessel function
    G_hat=np.nan_to_num(G_hat, copy=True, nan=1, posinf=None, neginf=None) # Taking into accont that lim x->0 of J1(x)/x = 1
    return G_hat

Gh=G_hat(Rk,R)
  • $\hat{G}$ is defined in the real space and one can write:
\begin{equation} G(\vec{r}) = \mathscr{F}^{-1} \{ \hat{G}(\vec{k}) \} = \begin{cases} \dfrac{1}{\pi R^2}, & \text{if $|\vec{r}| \leq R$} \\[1ex] 0, & \text{Otherwise}\end{cases} \end{equation}

Probability of surviving competition:¶

In [ ]:
def r(rho):
    pyfftw.interfaces.cache.enable() # Just optmizing things
    rho_hat=pyfftw.builders.fft2(rho,threads=3) # Taking \rho into the fourier space
    
    conv = pyfftw.builders.ifft2((Gh*rho_hat()),threads=3) # The convolution part
    
    return 1/(delta*conv().real +1) #Substituting in the function

Let:

${\displaystyle \tilde{\rho} = \int G(|\vec{r} - \vec{a}'|) \rho \; d\vec{a}.}$

Thus,

${\displaystyle \mathscr{F}\{\tilde{\rho}\} = \hat{G}(\vec{k}) \mathscr{F}\{\rho \}}$

Therfore, on the first 3 lines of the code we are obtaining $\tilde{\rho}$:

${\displaystyle \tilde{\rho} = \mathscr{F}^{-1} \big\{\hat{G}(\vec{k}) \mathscr{F}\{\rho \} \big \} }$

Then, in the last line of code we substitute $\tilde{\rho}$ in:

$\displaystyle r(\tilde{\rho},\delta) = \dfrac{1}{(1 + \delta \tilde{\rho})^{q}}$

The time derivative:¶

In [176]:
def Run_PDE(rho,K,L):

    return beta*r(rho)*rho*(1-rho)-alpha*rho

Basically:

$ {\displaystyle \dfrac{\partial \rho}{\partial t} = \beta_0 r(\tilde{\rho},\delta) \rho (1-\rho) - \alpha \rho}$
